producers.name: Constructor
producers.description: Crafts 1 part into another part.  Can be automated by feeding component parts in via a Conveyor Belt connected to the input port. The resulting parts can be automatically extracted by connecting a Conveyor Belt to the output port.

producers.name: Smelter
producers.description: Smelts ore into ingots.  Can be automated by feeding ore in via a Conveyor Belt connected to the input port. The resulting ingots can be automatically extracted by connecting a Conveyor Belt to the output port.

producers.name: Blender
producers.description: Blends fluids together or combines them with solid parts in a wide variety of processes. Head Lift: 10 m (Allows fluids to be transported 10 meters upwards.)  Has both Conveyor Belt and Pipeline input and output ports.

producers.name: Packager
producers.description: Packages and unpackages fluids. Head Lift: 10 m (Allows fluids to be transported 10 meters upwards.)  Contains both Conveyor Belt and Pipeline input and output ports so that a wide range of recipes can be automated.

producers.name: Converter
producers.description: The Converter harnesses Reanimated SAM to enable precise matter and energy transmutation.  Warning: Power usage is very high and unstable.

producers.name: Particle Accelerator
producers.description: Uses electromagnetic fields to propel particles to very high speeds and energies. The specific design allows for a variety of processes, including matter generation and conversion.  Warning: Power usage is extremely high and unstable, and varies per recipe.

producers.name: Quantum Encoder
producers.description: The Quantum Encoder uses Excited Photonic Matter to produce the most complex of parts, controlling development up to the quantum level.  Warning: Power usage is extremely high and unstable.

producers.name: Refinery
producers.description: Refines fluid and/or solid parts into other parts. Head Lift: 10 m (Allows fluids to be transported 10 meters upwards.)  Contains both Conveyor Belt and Pipeline input and output ports so that a wide range of recipes can be automated.

producers.name: Manufacturer
producers.description: Crafts 3 or 4 parts into another part.  Can be automated by feeding component parts in via Conveyor Belts connected to the input ports. The resulting parts can be automatically extracted by connecting a Conveyor Belt to the output port.

producers.name: Assembler
producers.description: Crafts 2 parts into another part.  Can be automated by feeding component parts in via Conveyor Belts connected to the input ports. The resulting parts can be automatically extracted by connecting a Conveyor Belt to the output port.

producers.name: Foundry
producers.description: Smelts 2 resources into alloy ingots.  Can be automated by feeding ore in via Conveyor Belts connected to the input ports. The resulting ingots can be automatically extracted by connecting a Conveyor Belt to the output port.

producers.name: Water Extractor
producers.description: Extracts water from the body of water it is built on. Note: the water needs to be sufficiently deep, and rivers are generally not deep enough.  Default Extraction Rate: 120 m³ of water per minute. Head Lift: 10 m (Allows fluids to be transported 10 meters upwards.)

producers.name: Oil Extractor
producers.description: Extracts Crude Oil when built on an oil node. Extraction rates vary based on node purity.  Default Extraction Rate: 120 m³ of oil per minute. Head Lift: 10 m (Allows fluids to be transported 10 meters upwards.)

producers.name: Miner Mk.2
producers.description: Extracts solid resources from the resource node it is built on.  Default extraction rate is 120 resources per minute.  Extraction rate varies based on resource node purity. Outputs all extracted resources onto connected Conveyor Belts.

producers.name: Miner Mk.1
producers.description: Extracts solid resources from the resource node it is built on.  Default extraction rate is 60 resources per minute.  Extraction rate varies based on resource node purity. Outputs all extracted resources onto connected Conveyor Belts.

producers.name: Miner Mk.3
producers.description: Extracts solid resources from the resource node it is built on.  Default extraction rate is 240 resources per minute.  Extraction rate varies based on resource node purity. Outputs all extracted resources onto connected Conveyor Belts.

producers.name: Resource Well Extractor
producers.description: Collects pressurized resources when placed on the activated sub-nodes of a Resource Well. Does not require power.  Default Extraction Rate: 60 m³ of fluid per minute. Head Lift: 10 m (Allows fluids to be transported 10 meters upwards.)

items.name: Iron Ingot
items.description: Used for crafting the most basic parts.

items.name: Iron Plate
items.description: Used for crafting. One of the most basic parts.

items.name: Iron Rod
items.description: Used for crafting. One of the most basic parts.

items.name: Iron Ore
items.description: Used for crafting. The most essential basic resource.

items.name: Fuel
items.description: Can be used as-is to generate power, or packaged to be used as fuel for vehicles or the Jetpack.

items.name: Nitrogen Gas
items.description: Has a variety of uses, including metallurgy, cooling, and Nitric Acid production. On MASSAGE-2 (AB)b, it can be extracted from underground gas wells.

items.name: Sulfur
items.description: Primarily used to produce Black Powder.

items.name: Coal
items.description: Mainly used as fuel for vehicles & Coal-Powered Generators, or in Steel production.

items.name: Rocket Fuel
items.description: A high-impulse compressed gas fuel. Can be used as-is to power Fuel-Powered Generators, or packaged to be used as fuel for vehicles or the Jetpack.

items.name: Compacted Coal
items.description: A much more efficient alternative to Coal. Used as fuel for vehicles and Coal-Powered Generators.

items.name: Turbofuel
items.description: A more efficient alternative to Fuel. Can be used as-is to generate power, or packaged to be used as fuel for vehicles.

items.name: Nitric Acid
items.description: Produced when Nitrogen Gas reacts with Water. Its high corrosiveness and oxidizing properties make it an excellent choice for refinement and fuel production processes.

items.name: Empty Fluid Tank
items.description: Used to package gases and volatile liquids for transportation.

items.name: Packaged Rocket Fuel
items.description: Rocket Fuel, packaged for alternative transport. Can be used as fuel for vehicles and the Jetpack.

items.name: Dark Matter Crystal
items.description: Concentrated Dark Matter Residue that is isolated within a crystalline vessel. This form of containment allows for utilising Dark Matter reliably in other production processes.  Power Usage: 500-1500 MW (1000 MW average).

items.name: Ionized Fuel
items.description: Fuel that has been ionized, allowing it to deliver incredible output. Can be used as-is to power Fuel-Powered Generators, or packaged to be used as fuel for vehicles or the Jetpack.

items.name: Reanimated SAM
items.description: The active and contained form of the Strange Alien Matter.  Proper electromagnetic containment is required, as it appears to be able to manipulate the atomic bonds of any matter it comes into contact with.

items.name: Dark Matter Residue
items.description: Produced as a by-product of Quantum Encoding processes and alternatively generated in the Converter.  Various fields of science are still debating the nature and properties of Dark Matter. Meanwhile, FICSIT has found several applications for it in space-time manipulation.

items.name: Excited Photonic Matter
items.description: Excited Photonic Matter is essential for all production processes in the Quantum Encoder.  Formed in the Converter by inducing intense photon interactions through exposure to SAM in a high-energy environment.

items.name: Diamonds
items.description: Synthetic Diamonds produced by exposing Coal to extreme heat and pressure.  Used in the production of Time Crystals and Dark Matter Crystals.  Power Usage: 250-750 MW (500 MW average).

items.name: Crystal Oscillator
items.description: An electronic oscillator circuit that uses the mechanical resonance of a vibrating crystal to create an electrical signal with a precise frequency.

items.name: Alclad Aluminum Sheet
items.description: Used to make products that require high heat conduction or a high specific strength. Thin, lightweight, and highly durable.

items.name: Superposition Oscillator
items.description: An oscillator circuit that uses the mechanical resonance of a vibrating crystal to create a string vibration with a precise frequency. Often used in teleportation technology and dimensional manipulation.

items.name: Time Crystal
items.description: Time Crystals are Diamonds that have been reconfigured on a sub-atomic level in the Converter to retain a time-periodic self-organizing structure. This allows them to be used in the development of quantum processing and storage technologies.

items.name: Supercomputer
items.description: The next-gen version of a Computer.

items.name: Ficsite Trigon
items.description: The Ficsite Trigon, made from Ficsite Ingots, is perfectly shaped for all construction challenges. It's performance is so exceptional, it basically solved structural engineering.

items.name: Neural-Quantum Processor
items.description: The Neural-Quantum Processor utilizes a combination of neural network architecture and quantum computing techniques to achieve unprecedented performance. This technology has enabled some of FICSIT's biggest advancements in artificial intelligence and relativistic engineering.

items.name: Magnetic Field Generator
items.description: Project Part #7. Ship via the Space Elevator to complete phases of Project Assembly.  These modular generators use superconducting magnets and vast amounts of electricity to produce a powerful and easily expandable magnetic field.

items.name: AI Expansion Server
items.description: Project Part #12. Ship via the Space Elevator to complete phases of Project Assembly. Power Usage: 1500-2500 MW (2000 MW average).  Growth is the metric by which we measure success.

items.name: Power Shard
items.description: Power Slug mucus compressed into a solid crystal-like shard.  It radiates a strange power.

items.name: Packaged Ionized Fuel
items.description: Ionized Fuel, packaged for alternative transport. Can be used as fuel for vehicles and the Jetpack.

items.name: Packaged Turbofuel
items.description: Turbofuel, packaged for alternative transport. Can be used as fuel for vehicles and the Jetpack.

items.name: Wire
items.description: Used for crafting. One of the most basic parts.

items.name: Steel Pipe
items.description: Primarily used when constructing slightly more advanced buildings.

items.name: SAM Fluctuator
items.description: The SAM Fluctuator is able to regulate and direct the behaviour of Reanimated SAM through the application of electric charges with varying frequencies. This control facilitates technologies such as matter-to-energy conversion and spatiotemporal matter manipulation.

items.name: Ficsite Ingot
items.description: Produced by reconstructing other metals on a molecular level using Strange Alien Matter.  Synthesized by FICSIT to be the perfect construction material, and used in the most high-end processes.

items.name: SAM
items.description: Strange Alien Matter, commonly referred to as SAM, doesn't seem to follow the known laws of physics. It whispers of new possibilities.

items.name: Assembly Director System
items.description: Project Part #6. Ship via the Space Elevator to complete phases of Project Assembly.  This extremely fast and precise computing system is specifically designed to direct the Project Assembly: Assembly Phase.

items.name: Water
items.description: It's water.

items.name: Biochemical Sculptor
items.description: Project Part #10. Ship via the Space Elevator to complete phases of Project Assembly.  Years ahead of the competition, this top-of-the-line 3D printer is used for the production of synthetic biological resources.

items.name: Aluminum Ingot
items.description: Smelted from Aluminum Scrap, which is refined from Alumina Solution. Used to produce specialized aluminum-based parts.

items.name: Caterium Ingot
items.description: Smelted from Caterium Ore. Primarily used for advanced electronics.

items.name: Caterium Ore
items.description: Smelted into Caterium Ingots, which are primarily used for advanced electronics.

items.name: Bauxite
items.description: Used to produce Alumina, which can be further refined into the Aluminum Scrap required to produce Aluminum Ingots.

items.name: Copper Ore
items.description: Used for crafting. A basic resource primarily used for electricity.

items.name: Raw Quartz
items.description: Can be processed into Quartz Crystals and Silica, which both offer a variety of applications.

items.name: Limestone
items.description: Used for crafting. A basic resource primarily used for stable Foundations.

items.name: Uranium
items.description: A radioactive element.  Used to produce Encased Uranium Cells for Uranium Fuel Rods.  Caution: Moderately Radioactive.

items.name: Empty Canister
items.description: Used to package fluids for transportation.

items.name: Wood
items.description: Primarily used as fuel. Biomass Burners and vehicles can use Wood for power.

items.name: Biomass
items.description: Primarily used as fuel. Biomass Burners and vehicles can use it for power. Biomass is much more energy-efficient than raw biological matter.

items.name: Copper Sheet
items.description: Used for crafting. Primarily used for Pipelines due to its high corrosion resistance.

items.name: Plastic
items.description: Versatile and easy to manufacture, this material has a wide range of uses.

items.name: Circuit Board
items.description: Advanced electronics that have a plethora of different uses.

items.name: Crude Oil
items.description: Refined into all kinds of Oil-based resources, like Fuel and Plastic.

items.name: Polymer Resin
items.description: A by-product of Crude Oil refinement into Fuel. Commonly used to manufacture Plastic and Rubber.

items.name: Heavy Oil Residue
items.description: A by-product of Plastic and Rubber production. Can be further refined into Fuel and Petroleum Coke.

items.name: Petroleum Coke
items.description: Used for crafting. A carbon-rich material distilled from Heavy Oil Residue.  Used as a less efficient Coal replacement.

items.name: Rubber
items.description: A very flexible material that has a lot of friction.

items.name: Quartz Crystal
items.description: Derived from Raw Quartz. Used in the production of advanced radar technology and high-quality display screens.

items.name: Concrete
items.description: Used for building. Good for stable Foundations.

items.name: Steel Ingot
items.description: Smelted from a combination of Iron Ore and Coal. Can be made into several parts used in building construction.

items.name: Steel Beam
items.description: Primarily used when constructing slightly more advanced buildings.

items.name: Modular Frame
items.description: Used for crafting. A multipurpose building block.

items.name: Versatile Framework
items.description: Project Part #2. Ship via the Space Elevator to complete phases of Project Assembly.

items.name: Packaged Fuel
items.description: Fuel, packaged for alternative transport. Can be used as fuel for vehicles and the Jetpack.

items.name: Solid Biofuel
items.description: The most energy-efficient form of solid Biomass. Can be used as fuel for the Chainsaw.

items.name: Liquid Biofuel
items.description: Liquid Biofuel can be used as-is to generate power, or packaged to be used as fuel for vehicles.

items.name: Packaged Liquid Biofuel
items.description: Liquid Biofuel, packaged for alternative transport. Can be used as fuel for vehicles and the Jetpack.

items.name: Packaged Oil
items.description: Crude Oil, packaged for alternative transport. Can be used as fuel for vehicles.

items.name: Packaged Heavy Oil Residue
items.description: Heavy Oil Residue, packaged for alternative transport. Can be used as fuel for vehicles.

items.name: Packaged Water
items.description: Water, packaged for alternative transport.

items.name: Copper Ingot
items.description: Used for crafting the most basic parts.

items.name: Aluminum Scrap
items.description: Refined from Alumina. Can be smelted into Aluminum Ingots for industrial usage.

items.name: Aluminum Casing
items.description: A versatile container cast from Aluminum Ingots.

items.name: Alumina Solution
items.description: Dissolved Alumina, extracted from Bauxite. Can be further refined into Aluminum Scrap for Aluminum Ingot production.

items.name: Silica
items.description: Derived from Raw Quartz. Commonly used to create glass structures, in advanced refinement processes, and for alternative production of electronics.

items.name: Packaged Alumina Solution
items.description: Alumina Solution, packaged for alternative transport.

items.name: Cable
items.description: Used for crafting. Primarily used to build Power Lines.

items.name: Reinforced Iron Plate
items.description: Used for crafting. A sturdier and more durable Iron Plate.

items.name: Rotor
items.description: Used for crafting. The moving parts of a motor.

items.name: Smart Plating
items.description: Project Part #1. Ship via the Space Elevator to complete phases of Project Assembly.

items.name: Stator
items.description: Used for crafting. The static parts of a motor.

items.name: High-Speed Connector
items.description: Connects multiple cables and wires in a very efficient way. Uses a standard pattern, so it has many varied applications.

items.name: Automated Wiring
items.description: Project Part #3. Ship via the Space Elevator to complete phases of Project Assembly.

items.name: Encased Industrial Beam
items.description: Simultaneously utilizes the compressive strength of concrete and the tensile strength of steel. Mostly used as a stable base for constructing buildings.

items.name: Motor
items.description: Creates a mechanical force that is used to move things from machines to vehicles.

items.name: Quickwire
items.description: Caterium's high conductivity and resistance to corrosion make it ideal for small, advanced electronics.

items.name: AI Limiter
items.description: Controls AIs and keeps them from evolving in malicious ways. Super advanced electronics.

items.name: Screw
items.description: Used for crafting. One of the most basic parts.

items.name: Heavy Modular Frame
items.description: A more robust multipurpose frame.

items.name: Computer
items.description: A complex logic machine that is used to control advanced behavior in other machines.

items.name: Modular Engine
items.description: Project Part #4. Ship via the Space Elevator to complete phases of Project Assembly.

items.name: Adaptive Control Unit
items.description: Project Part #5. Ship via the Space Elevator to complete phases of Project Assembly.

items.name: Pressure Conversion Cube
items.description: Converts outgoing force into internal pressure. Required to contain unstable, high-energy matter.

items.name: Packaged Nitrogen Gas
items.description: Nitrogen Gas, packaged for alternative transport.

items.name: Turbo Motor
items.description: A more complex and powerful version of the regular Motor.

items.name: Plutonium Pellet
items.description: Produced in the Particle Accelerator through conversion of Non-fissile Uranium. Used to produce Encased Plutonium Cells for Plutonium Fuel Rods.  Power Usage: 250-750 MW (500 MW average). Caution: Moderately Radioactive.

items.name: Encased Plutonium Cell
items.description: Plutonium Pellets encased in concrete. Used to produce Plutonium Fuel Rods for Nuclear Power production.  Caution: Moderately Radioactive.

items.name: Fused Modular Frame
items.description: A corrosion-resistant, nitride-hardened, highly-robust-yet-lightweight modular frame.

items.name: Radio Control Unit
items.description: Enhances and directs radio signals.

items.name: Uranium Waste
items.description: The by-product of consuming Uranium Fuel Rods in a Nuclear Power Plant. Non-Fissile Uranium can be extracted. Handle with caution.  Caution: HIGHLY Radioactive.

items.name: Sulfuric Acid
items.description: Produced by combining Sulfur and Water in a complex reaction. Primarily used in refinement processes and Battery production.

items.name: Non-Fissile Uranium
items.description: The Uranium-238 isotope is non-fissile, meaning it cannot be used for nuclear fission. It can, however, be converted into fissile Plutonium in the Particle Accelerator.  Caution: Mildly Radioactive.

items.name: Copper Powder
items.description: Ground-up Copper Ingots. The high natural density of Copper, combined with the granularity of the powder, makes this part perfect for producing Nuclear Pasta in the Particle Accelerator.

items.name: Electromagnetic Control Rod
items.description: Regulates power output via electromagnetism.

items.name: Heat Sink
items.description: Used to dissipate heat faster.

items.name: Plutonium Fuel Rod
items.description: Used as fuel for Nuclear Power Plants.  Caution: Produces radioactive Plutonium Waste when consumed. Caution: HIGHLY Radioactive.

items.name: Packaged Nitric Acid
items.description: Nitric Acid, packaged for alternative transport.

items.name: Nuclear Pasta
items.description: Project Part #9. Ship via the Space Elevator to complete phases of Project Assembly. Power Usage: 500-1500 MW (1000 MW average).  Nuclear Pasta is extremely dense degenerate matter, formed when extreme pressure forces protons and electrons together into neutrons. It is theorized to exist naturally within the crust of neutron stars.

items.name: Encased Uranium Cell
items.description: Used to produce Uranium Fuel Rods for Nuclear Power production. Made from Uranium Ore.  Caution: Mildly Radioactive.

items.name: Cooling System
items.description: Keeps advanced parts and buildings from exceeding efficient temperature levels.

items.name: Battery
items.description: Primarily used as fuel for Drones and vehicles.

items.name: Packaged Sulfuric Acid
items.description: Sulfuric Acid, packaged for alternative transport.

items.name: Uranium Fuel Rod
items.description: Used as fuel for Nuclear Power Plants.  Caution: Produces radioactive Uranium Waste when consumed. Caution: Moderately Radioactive.

items.name: Dissolved Silica
items.description: Silica dissolved in Water, produced as part of the alternative refinement of Raw Quartz. The Silica can be extracted from the Water to complete the refinement process.

items.name: Thermal Propulsion Rocket
items.description: Project Part #8. Ship via the Space Elevator to complete phases of Project Assembly.  Uses extreme heat to produce the high-pressure plasma required to get Project Assembly into motion.

items.name: Black Powder
items.description: An explosive powder that is commonly used to produce simple explosives.

items.name: Plutonium Waste
items.description: The by-product of consuming Plutonium Fuel Rods in a Nuclear Power Plant. Must be stored in a safe location. Handle with caution.  Caution: EXTREMELY Radioactive.

items.name: Singularity Cell
items.description: Used to break down space and time. Required to power Portals.

items.name: Ficsonium
items.description: Usage and production of this material is strictly prohibited. On Earth, that is. There are no rules in space, only efficiency.   Power Usage: 500-1500 MW (1000 MW average).

items.name: Ficsonium Fuel Rod
items.description: Used as fuel for Nuclear Power Plants. The power source that put FICSIT on the map. Literally. The crater is still there.  Caution: Moderately Radioactive.

items.name: Ballistic Warp Drive
items.description: Project Part #11. Ship via the Space Elevator to complete phases of Project Assembly. Power Usage: 1000-2000 MW (1500 MW average).  A large amount of force is required for the Warp Drives to activate, so sticking them to rockets was the logical next step. Additionally, results improved immensely when the observers were further removed from the Warp Drives upon activation.

items.name: Gas Filter
items.description: Filters out toxins and pollutants from the air when used with a Gas Mask.

items.name: Iodine-Infused Filter
items.description: Absorbs radioactive particles when used with the Hazmat Suit.

items.name: Hog Remains
items.description: The carapace of an alien Hog creature. Used for MAM research.

items.name: Alien Protein
items.description: Ground-up Alien Remains in a neat little package. Used for medical purposes and to research alien organisms.

items.name: Spitter Remains
items.description: The remains of a plasma-spitting alien creature. Used for MAM research.

items.name: Mycelia
items.description: Used for crafting. Biomass Burners and vehicles can also use Mycelia for power.

items.name: Blue Power Slug
items.description: A strange slug radiating an unknown weak power.

items.name: Alien Power Matrix
items.description: This intricate condensed-matter matrix is used to enhance the output of the Alien Power Augmenter.   Initially developed in efforts to create a human-made Somersloop, the Alien Power Matrix cannot sustain the extra-dimensional energy connection on its own. However, it can effectively stabilize the energy stream of the Somersloop.

items.name: Stinger Remains
items.description: The remains of whatever that creepy thing was. Used for MAM research.

items.name: Hatcher Remains
items.description: The shell-like remains of an alien... thing. Used for MAM research.

items.name: Alien DNA Capsule
items.description: Translates organic chemicals into readable alien genetic information. Used for researching alien organisms.  Go the extra kilometer! Knowledge is power, and power is just efficiency with fewer steps. Depositing Alien DNA Capsules in the AWESOME Sink provides FICSIT with knowledge, and pioneers with Coupons.

items.name: Iron Rebar
items.description: Can be shot using the Rebar Gun for self-defense purposes.

items.name: Rifle Ammo
items.description: Standard issue Rifle ammunition, useful for establishing dominance.

items.name: Homing Rifle Ammo
items.description: The bullet guidance system built into this ammunition allows it to accurately hit any target within the reticle area. Especially useful when dealing with agile threats, or for pioneers who can't be bothered to aim properly.

items.name: Stun Rebar
items.description: Electrocutes the target on impact, stunning it for a short time.  Stun Duration: 5 seconds

items.name: Fabric
items.description: Used to craft equipment. Flexible but durable fabric.

items.name: Nobelisk
items.description: A simple explosive, useful for clearing boulders, vegetation, and other obstacles.

items.name: Gas Nobelisk
items.description: Creates a deadly gas cloud instead of a regular explosion.

items.name: Purple Power Slug
items.description: A strange slug radiating a powerful unknown power.

items.name: Yellow Power Slug
items.description: A strange slug radiating an unknown power.

items.name: Pulse Nobelisk
items.description: Generates a powerful shockwave instead of a regular explosion.

items.name: Shatter Rebar
items.description: Fractures when shot, launching deadly debris with wide spread but limited range.

items.name: Turbo Rifle Ammo
items.description: Lightweight, compact, and volatile. These rounds provide extreme capacity and rate of fire at the cost of accuracy.

items.name: Smokeless Powder
items.description: An explosive powder that is commonly used to produce modern firearms.

items.name: Nuke Nobelisk
items.description: Uses a nuclear fission reaction to generate a massive explosion. WARNING: Ensure all FICSIT property is clear of the blast zone before detonation.

items.name: Explosive Rebar
items.description: Explodes on impact, dealing heavy damage.

items.name: Cluster Nobelisk
items.description: Detonates into multiple smaller explosions. Practical for clearing out large areas of vegetation and other inconveniences.

items.name: Actual Snow
items.description: It's snow. Not the nice, thick, crunchy kind, though... more the disgustingly wet, slushy kind... Guess we can make stuff from it.

items.name: Snowball
items.description: Compressed dihydrogen monoxide crystals.

items.name: FICSMAS Decoration
items.description: A decoration used to make decorations. Its use cases are questionable.

items.name: Candy Cane
items.description: A delicious Candy Cane to be enjoyed during the FICSMAS Holidays.  *Disclaimer: Not for consumption...

items.name: FICSMAS Wonder Star
items.description: This special FICSMAS Star signifies FICSIT's productivity all across the universe. It also signifies the fact that you have nearly completed the Holiday Event, so it's time to get back to work.

items.name: FICSMAS Tree Branch
items.description: A special Tree Branch used to produce parts and buildings during the FICSMAS Event.

items.name: FICSMAS Ornament Bundle
items.description: All the FICSMAS Ornaments smashed together to make even more FICSMAS Decorations!

items.name: Copper FICSMAS Ornament
items.description: Still used for making FICSMAS Decorations.

items.name: Iron FICSMAS Ornament
items.description: A super special- Nope! Still just used for making FICSMAS Decorations.

items.name: FICSMAS Gift
items.description: Special FICSMAS buildings and parts can be obtained and produced from this FICSIT Holiday present.  *Watch the sky for deliveries from orbit!

items.name: Red FICSMAS Ornament
items.description: Used for making FICSMAS Decorations.

items.name: Blue FICSMAS Ornament
items.description: Again, used for making FICSMAS Decorations.

items.name: FICSMAS Bow
items.description: A fancy Bow. Maybe someone could wear this? You certainly can't! What you can do is make parts and decorations from it. Probably.

items.name: Leaves
items.description: Primarily used as fuel. Biomass Burners and vehicles can use Leaves for power.

items.name: Sweet Fireworks
items.description: Merry FICSMAS and a Happy New Year!

items.name: Fancy Fireworks
items.description: Fireworks are produced from random ingredients. Primarily used for having a good time.

items.name: Sparkly Fireworks
items.description: Goes Pfffeeeeew... BOOM! *Sparkle*
